dreams.dream: I had a dream where I met my boss. He was working as a clerk in a meat food store. Before I entered the store I had to cross the road. At first the cars were not stopping to let me pass but I walked over the crosswalk with confidence and the cars stopped in front of me. I jogged to the other side of the street. When I entered the food store, I ordered a product and he told me to come back a bit later. When I did, he offered me a chicken kebab product. I bought it. It was a finely packed and I was happy with the purchase. Then I left.
dreams.interpretation:
This dream may symbolize your relationship with your boss and the dynamics of power and confidence in your professional life. The fact that your boss is working as a clerk in a meat food store suggests a role reversal or a shift in power dynamics. It could indicate that you feel empowered or in control in your waking life, as evidenced by your ability to confidently cross the road and have the cars stop for you.

The act of ordering a product and being told to come back later may represent delayed gratification or a need for patience in achieving your goals. When you return, your boss offers you a chicken kebab product, which could symbolize a reward or opportunity that is being presented to you. The fact that you purchase the product and are happy with it suggests that you are satisfied with the opportunities that come your way and are willing to seize them.

Overall, this dream may be reflecting your sense of empowerment and confidence within your professional life, as well as your ability to recognize and seize opportunities when they arise. It may also indicate a positive relationship or positive dynamics with your boss.
dreams.title: The Meat Clerk's Surprise: A Crosswalk triumph and a Chicken Kabab Delight

dreams.dream: It is a recurring dream I've had several times during my life. I'm in my flat on the first floor. Suddenly the whole building starts tilting to the side, and it falls down as if it is a box or a domino piece. The building stays intact, but inside the flat all furniture and other objects are falling, crushing and making a mess. Surprisingly, I am uninjured.
dreams.interpretation:
Dreams about buildings collapsing or falling can often symbolize a feeling of instability or insecurity in your life. Being in your own flat on the first floor may represent a sense of familiarity and comfort within your personal life or relationships.

The fact that the whole building tilts to the side and falls down like a box or a domino piece suggests that something in your life is out of balance or fragile. This could indicate that you are currently experiencing some upheaval or disruption in your life, which is causing you to feel a lack of control.

The furniture and objects falling, crushing, and making a mess inside the flat could represent the chaos and disorder that this instability has caused. This may reflect the emotional turmoil or confusion you are experiencing as a result of the circumstances.

The fact that you are uninjured in the dream might indicate that even though it feels like everything is falling apart, you have an inner strength and resilience that allows you to stay unharmed. It suggests that despite the challenges you face, you have the ability to navigate through difficult situations and come out stronger on the other side.

Overall, this recurring dream may be a reflection of your subconscious concerns or anxieties about instability in your life. It could be helpful to explore any unresolved issues, seek support if needed, and work towards finding a sense of stability and balance in your waking life.
dreams.title: Toppling Horizons: Unscathed Amidst the Chaotic Collapse

dreams.dream: I was in a bungalow. Looking through the window I saw that everywhere outside there was water. Like a house was built in the middle of a lake. Or like there has been a flood, since there where a few tree tops visible . Near my house I saw a sheep. It was standing in the water, it's head above the water. It was calm.
dreams.interpretation:
The dream you described can be interpreted as symbolizing both emotions and a sense of stability amidst challenging circumstances. The bungalow represents a personal and private space within your subconscious mind. The water surrounding the bungalow signifies emotions, which in this case may be overwhelming or excessively present in your life.

The flood or the lake suggests that you may be facing a situation or a challenge that feels all-encompassing or difficult to navigate. The tree tops represent elements of stability or hope that are still visible amidst the flood, indicating that even in challenging times, there are still positive aspects to hold onto.

The sheep standing calmly in the water is a symbol of inner peace and resilience. It represents your ability to remain composed and maintain a level-headed approach during trying times. The sheep's head being above the water indicates your ability to maintain a clear perspective and make rational decisions, even when emotions are running high.

Overall, this dream reflects your capacity to stay grounded and find tranquility amidst uncertainty or turmoil. It suggests that you possess inner strength and resilience that will help you navigate and overcome challenging situations in your waking life.
dreams.title: The Surreal Serenity: A Bungalow Amidst a Watery Wonderland

An umbrella is often seen as a symbol of protection or shelter from the rain or challenging circumstances. The horse swimming in an umbrella could represent your ability to adapt and find security in unexpected or unusual ways. It may suggest that you are effectively handling difficult situations and finding creative solutions to challenges.

Overall, this dream could symbolize your ability to find strength, protection, and adaptability in challenging or unconventional circumstances. Invited lotta ppl and when they came, i stood on top of this house on like a little balcony, where you can unfold it and was like, ‘i know this seems small and shit but now look at this’. 2 floors, 4 jacuzzis, big bar, 2 floor library (idk why). The weirdest but coolest thing was that the living room could be a pool. It was like hawaiian party mansion. Great, great, great. Rating this 5 on yelp.

The party you threw could represent your desire to share your success with others. The fact that the living room could turn into a pool could symbolize your desire for fun and relaxation in your life. Overall, this dream may suggest that you have a subconscious desire for more comfort, luxury, and enjoyment in your life.
